I went here about a month ago with my husband and we had a great time. We liked the beer selection and funky decor, but the best part was the service. Our bartender Erin was fantastic - we just moved to NYC and she gave us so many great tips on useful apps for the city, the most interesting museums, and good restaurants and bars in the Brooklyn neighborhood we mentioned we were eyeing in our apartment search. I just remembered to leave this review when we used one of her recommended apps, haha. If we’re up in the area we will make it a point to stop in again!

Taps here are fantastic. Great staff and atmosphere. The bottle and can program (to stay or take out) is unlike anything I've ever seen. My favorite bar in NYC, hands down.

I'm not sure (nor do I care really) if this place is a true dive, but they do have an unexpectedly vast selection of bottled beer. It's extremely narrow and can be hard to maneuver around, and the crowd is, well, what you'd expect in the UWS. One of the older female bartenders is often rude and unatentive to me personally, but all the others are fine. The biggest pain in the ass about the bar is that only some of the bottles are priced, so it means you either have to spend several minutes thumbing through their menu online to check the price of each beer or just be hit with the surprise when you go to be rung up. I never stick around because of the corkage fee/crowd, but after work this is a good place to pick up something yummy and head back to Brooklyn.
